data.name: William Rice
data.bio: Former police officer turned software developer. I am passionate about learning new technologies and helping others learn as well. Check out my website at https://williamarice.com

data.name: William Burroughs
data.bio: William Burroughs is the founder of C4C, a club that helps programmers build their skills and resumes while giving back to their communities. William is a software architect at SkyFi. He is skilled in Ruby, JavaScript, and Swift. He currently has 5 apps listed on the iPhone app store, the most recent being The Space Project, a retro space-themed arcade shooter. Outside of work, he enjoys learning Italian and playing racquetball.

data.name: Ofir Klein
data.bio: Ofir Klein is an autodidactic programmer with a diverse background spanning data engineering, software development, data analytics, and GIS. He's built programs for data migrations, data integrations, Machine Learning, natural language processing, and UI/UX design, and specialize in architecting scalable, composable, and maintainable systems. With experience in both technical and creative domains, his design principle is to create products that lasts: the best solutions, he argues, are those that are simple, but not simplistic, growable, and able to adapt and evolve over time.

data.name: Neal Powers
data.bio: I'm a software developer from Lexington, working primarily in Laravel. I've been a teacher and play the trumpet! I'm super interested in Golang and all things web dev!

data.name: David York
data.bio: I work to help people succeed! My professional experience lies in managing people, creating strong relationships, and goal achievement. I'm always interested in new ideas and creative problem solving. Reach out to me on LinkedIn or Discord!
